[normal]Now, these are the responsible lending things that 
[normal]are very high-level, and repeatedly we see in credit markets that high-level lending rules
[normal] have not worked
[normal]. 
[normal]You give 
[normal]firms some guidance, and then come back and look later. As well as real
[normal]­
[normal]time data sharing, because these products have got such a short-term duration and the risk can build up so quickly, 
[normal]maybe the regulator also needs to be getting its 
[normal]data in real time so it can spot wrongdoing as it is happening and intervene, rather than coming back months or
[normal] years later
[normal]. 
[normal]The other thing is looking at how these
[normal] products work. If the average income of our clients with a payday loan is about £1,250, can they
[normal] afford to repay £500
[normal]? 
[normal]That is nearly 
[normal]50% of your net household income a 
[normal]month
[normal]. 
[normal]How is that affordable
[normal]? 
[normal]If you have got people offering up to £1,000, there is 
