[normal]Martin Lewis[bold]: To follow up from that,
[normal] the real struggle is, since November 2009, you have had a right to go to your bank and cancel a CPA, but you call up the bank and the bank staff do not know that, and they tell you that you cannot
[normal]. 
[normal]People are right to say
[normal],
[normal] “I cannot cancel it
[normal],”
[normal] because they try
[normal] to
[normal] cancel
[normal],
[normal] and they do not
[normal]. 
[normal]We have a real problem
[normal]—
[normal]not just within payday loans; CPA is an issue right across the board
[normal]—of being 
[normal]un
[normal]able to cancel 
[normal]that type of payment
[normal]. 
[normal]Sometimes the public are right: you cannot cancel it, even though you have a right to.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q140 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Nadhim Zahawi:[bold] Briefly, on that one, we heard from the panel previous to you
[normal]—from Mr Lender—
[normal]that CPAs
[normal] can be a really good thing for the customer
[normal]. 
[normal]It took me about 30 seconds to get something up here from 
[normal]the 
