[normal]Initially, the industry had committed that they would review their own compliance on that, but when it came to the crunch, unfortunately, not all of the industry was prepared to undertake that review
[normal]. 
[normal]As the Department, we initiated our own surveys to try to test the extent to which there was compliance with the industry’s 
[normal]voluntary codes, and what we found was pretty disappointing in terms of compliance
[normal]. 
[normal]One in five customers reported that the lender did not ask about their finances when they were taking out a loan, and this rose to 60% when they were actually rolling over that loan
